---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Visa Sponsored Tech Jobs in the UK | Software Engineering & More"
description: "Find visa-sponsored tech jobs in the United Kingdom with relocation assistance. Browse software engineering, data science, and fintech roles in London, Manchester, Edinburgh and more."
permalink: /jobs-in-uk/
---

{% set country_name = "United Kingdom" %}
{% set country_flag = "🇬🇧" %}
{% set grouped = jobs | groupByCountry %}
{% set ukJobs1 = grouped["United Kingdom"] or [] %}
{% set ukJobs2 = grouped["UK"] or [] %}
{% set totalUkJobs = (ukJobs1 | length) + (ukJobs2 | length) %}

{% block structuredData %}
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "{{ site.url }}/" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Jobs by Country", "item": "{{ site.url }}/jobs-by-country/" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "United Kingdom", "item": "{{ site.url }}/jobs-in-uk/" }
  ]
}
</script>
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "CollectionPage",
  "name": "Visa Sponsored Tech Jobs in the United Kingdom",
  "description": "Find {{ totalUkJobs }}+ visa-sponsored tech jobs in the UK with relocation assistance.",
  "url": "{{ site.url }}/jobs-in-uk/",
  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "{{ site.name }}", "url": "{{ site.url }}" },
  "mainEntity": {
    "@type": "ItemList",
    "numberOfItems": {{ totalUkJobs }},
    "itemListElement": [
      {% set schemaIdx = 1 %}
      {% for job in ukJobs1 | limit(10) %}
      {
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": {{ schemaIdx }},
        "item": {
          "@type": "JobPosting",
          "title": "{{ job.position }}",
          "datePosted": "{{ job.post_date }}",
          "description": "{{ job.position }} at {{ job.company }} in {{ job.location }}. Visa sponsorship and relocation assistance included.",
          "employmentType": "FULL_TIME",
          "hiringOrganization": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "{{ job.company }}",
            "logo": "{{ site.url }}{{ job.logo }}"
          },
          "jobLocation": {
            "@type": "Place",
            "address": { "@type": "PostalAddress", "addressCountry": "GB", "addressLocality": "{{ job.location }}" }
          },
          "url": "{{ job.description }}"
        }
      },
      {% set schemaIdx = schemaIdx + 1 %}
      {% endfor %}
      {% for job in ukJobs2 | limit(10) %}
      {
        "@type": "ListItem",
        "position": {{ schemaIdx }},
        "item": {
          "@type": "JobPosting",
          "title": "{{ job.position }}",
          "datePosted": "{{ job.post_date }}",
          "description": "{{ job.position }} at {{ job.company }} in {{ job.location }}. Visa sponsorship and relocation assistance included.",
          "employmentType": "FULL_TIME",
          "hiringOrganization": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "{{ job.company }}",
            "logo": "{{ site.url }}{{ job.logo }}"
          },
          "jobLocation": {
            "@type": "Place",
            "address": { "@type": "PostalAddress", "addressCountry": "GB", "addressLocality": "{{ job.location }}" }
          },
          "url": "{{ job.description }}"
        }
      }{% if not loop.last %},{% endif %}
      {% set schemaIdx = schemaIdx + 1 %}
      {% endfor %}
    ]
  }
}
</script>
{% endblock %}

{# Hero #}
<section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-brand-50 to-white dark:from-gray-900 dark:to-gray-950 py-12 md:py-16">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
    <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-brand-600 dark:hover:text-brand-400 transition-colors">Home</a>
      <i data-lucide="chevron-right" class="w-3.5 h-3.5"></i>
      <a href="/jobs-by-country/" class="hover:text-brand-600 dark:hover:text-brand-400 transition-colors">Jobs by Country</a>
      <i data-lucide="chevron-right" class="w-3.5 h-3.5"></i>
      <span class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white font-medium">United Kingdom</span>
    </nav>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
      <span class="text-5xl">{{ country_flag }}</span>
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white tracking-tight">
          Tech Jobs in the UK
        </h1>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">
          {{ totalUkJobs }} visa-sponsored positions with relocation assistance
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-6">
      <span class="badge badge-visa">Visa Sponsorship</span>
      <span class="badge badge-reloc">Relocation Assistance</span>
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
        <i data-lucide="map-pin" class="w-3.5 h-3.5"></i>
        London, Manchester, Edinburgh & more
      </span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# Job Listings #}
<section class="py-12">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-6">
      <h2 class="section-heading">All Positions</h2>
      <span class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">{{ totalUkJobs }} jobs</span>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      {% for job in jobs %}
      {% if "United Kingdom" in job.location or "UK 🇬🇧" in job.location %}
      <div class="job-card">
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-start gap-4">
          <img src="{{ job.logo }}" alt="{{ job.company }}" class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg object-cover shrink-0" loading="lazy" onerror="this.src='/favicon/android-chrome-192x192.png'">
          <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-1">{{ job.position }}</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-2">{{ job.company }}</p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-4 gap-y-1 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">
              <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
                <i data-lucide="map-pin" class="w-3.5 h-3.5"></i>
                {{ job.location }}
              </span>
              <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
                <i data-lucide="clock" class="w-3.5 h-3.5"></i>
                {{ job.post_date | timeAgo }}
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              {% if job.reloc %}<span class="badge badge-reloc">{{ job.reloc }}</span>{% endif %}
              {% if job.visa %}<span class="badge badge-visa">{{ job.visa }}</span>{% endif %}
              <span class="badge badge-contract">{{ job.contract }}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <a href="{{ job.description }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="job-card-apply">
            Apply <i data-lucide="external-link" class="w-3.5 h-3.5 ml-1.5"></i>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
      {% endif %}
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# SEO Content #}
<section class="py-12 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900/50">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Working in the UK as a Tech Professional</h2>
    <p>
      The United Kingdom remains one of the world's top destinations for tech talent. London is Europe's leading fintech hub and hosts a massive startup ecosystem, while cities like Manchester, Edinburgh, Bristol, and Cambridge offer growing tech communities with lower costs of living. The UK's global reach, English-speaking environment, and diverse culture make it particularly attractive for international professionals.
    </p>
    <p>
      Since Brexit, the UK operates a points-based immigration system. The <strong>Skilled Worker visa</strong> (which replaced the Tier 2 visa) is the primary route for tech professionals. You need a job offer from a licensed sponsor, and the role must meet minimum salary thresholds (generally £38,700 or the going rate for the role). Tech roles typically qualify as shortage occupations, which can lower requirements. Processing is relatively fast, usually 3–8 weeks.
    </p>
    <p>
      UK tech salaries are competitive, especially in London where senior engineers can earn £80,000–£120,000+. The work culture balances professionalism with flexibility, and many companies offer hybrid or remote arrangements. The NHS provides universal healthcare, and after five years you can apply for settlement (Indefinite Leave to Remain).
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

